Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.15,0:01:17.59,Default,Mikami,0,0,0,,Well then, you two be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.77,0:01:18.45,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.55,0:01:44.12,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,How was Nakao that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.22,0:01:49.07,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,He was carsick, \Nso he threw up a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.50,0:01:50.46,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:52.19,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.64,0:01:54.92,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,He couldn't swim well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.83,0:01:58.14,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.59,0:02:00.96,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,So, maybe he was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.96,0:02:02.26,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.68,0:02:11.02,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Well, I spoke with the detective, Mr. Ohba, about what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.46,0:02:12.84,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,His suspicion was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:17.92,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,...that Nakao might have died \Nbefore the boat hit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.29,0:02:24.43,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,The injury found on his head was\Ninconsistent with the collision to the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.82,0:02:29.39,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,The cistern obliteration, caused by cerebral \Ncontusion, had already progressed significantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.39,0:02:31.68,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So it happened before \Nwe went to the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.24,0:02:35.36,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,According to his family,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.36,0:02:39.53,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,they heard a loud bang from \Nthe staircase that morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.31,0:02:41.95,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,When they went to take a look,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.95,0:02:46.01,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,all they saw was Nakao \Nhurrying out of the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.01,0:02:48.39,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,He must have hit his head then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:49.51,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.68,0:02:55.98,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So the event that led to his \Ndeath took place in Yomiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.18,0:02:58.53,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,We can safely assume that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.89,0:03:06.07,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Leaving Yomiyama without first going \Nto the hospital assured his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:15.55,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Hey, Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.53,0:03:17.24,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:22.30,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No, never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.73,0:03:25.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I'll tell you after I find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:27.47,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.69,0:03:32.71,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Did you find that class \Nphoto from 26 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.60,0:03:34.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.23,0:03:59.59,Default,Yukari,0,0,0,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:06.80,Default,Takabayashi,0,0,0,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.32,0:04:12.85,Default,Kubodera,0,0,0,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.02,0:04:18.69,Default,Mizuno,0,0,0,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.51,0:04:21.52,Default,Nakao,0,0,0,,It's your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.87,0:04:38.88,Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\4c&H332A29&\1a&H55&\fnSteinem Unicode\fay-0.18\fs38\shad3\pos(880,366)\fsp3\fscy76\c&HCBB9A8&}I{\fscy100}noya
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.10,0:04:40.23,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,The classroom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.55,0:04:48.40,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Did he really say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.98,0:04:51.43,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yeah, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.43,0:04:56.52,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,He must mean ninth grade's \Nclass 3 in the old building.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:59.23,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,What did he hide?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.94,0:05:06.34,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I see. At the very least, \Nwe have a location.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.34,0:05:07.42,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I'll just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.42,0:05:08.59,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:10.53,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Don't tell anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:12.59,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.01,0:05:16.07,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,If Nakao hadn't gone \Nto the beach with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.07,0:05:17.58,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,he probably wouldn't have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:19.75,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.75,0:05:23.18,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,That's why I don't want to \Nget anyone else involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.18,0:05:26.04,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I don't want \Nanyone else to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.79,0:05:30.98,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We shouldn't tell Akazawa, or the \Ncountermeasures committee just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.61,0:05:33.20,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,If we do find something,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.20,0:05:37.04,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,and if we need their help, \Nwe'll tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.48,0:05:39.05,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:42.38,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I don't want to see Akazawa die.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.38,0:05:46.32,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,So when should we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.32,0:05:48.02,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,We aren't going right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.02,0:05:50.58,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,I have plans with \Nmy family tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.95,0:05:52.34,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Tomorrow's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.34,0:05:54.66,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,How about first thing \Nin the morning, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:57.37,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,C'mon! Not the morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.37,0:05:59.12,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Okay... How about at noon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:02.81,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,There'll be a lot of \Nclub members around,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.81,0:06:06.59,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,and since the second \Nfloor is blocked off...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.76,0:06:08.55,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Okay... How about \Nin the evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:11.38,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,It's harder to look \Nfor stuff at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:15.01,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Fine. We'll go at \Nthree o'clock, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.28,0:06:15.97,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.97,0:06:16.76,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.76,0:06:20.11,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Mochizuki, the art club meets \Nin the old building, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.11,0:06:21.40,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:23.42,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Do any club members \Ncome during summer break?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.82,0:06:25.23,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,No, never.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.23,0:06:28.07,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,So can we meet \Nin the club room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:29.05,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:30.89,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,I have a key,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.89,0:06:33.78,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,and no one would \Nquestion my being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.18,0:06:38.71,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Teshigawara, please don't \Nshow up dressed like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:40.44,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.44,0:06:41.70,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You'll stand out.
