Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:04.01,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Oh? Is that Kouichi and Teshy? {Teshi? Teshy?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.41,0:07:06.90,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,What are the aces of the \Ngo-home club doing at school?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:09.30,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Nothing, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.30,0:07:11.56,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,We're meeting up with Mochizuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.56,0:07:13.61,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Are you two here for club stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.59,0:07:18.41,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,We wanted to meet \Nwith Mr. Chibiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.28,0:07:20.54,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,In the auxiliary library?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:22.76,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Not for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.20,0:07:25.83,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Mr. Chibiki is the \Ndrama club's advisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.83,0:07:26.95,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.95,0:07:28.39,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,The guy who wears \Nnothing but black?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.78,0:07:29.80,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I didn't expect that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:33.71,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,He actually gives \Ngood acting advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.71,0:07:37.62,Default,Ogura,0,0,0,,He also looks kinda cool \Nwhen he's acting. It's fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.99,0:07:38.64,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.16,0:07:40.85,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Why exactly are you two here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.40,0:07:48.99,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We're looking for a clue \Nto help stop the calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.56,0:07:51.44,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We don't know what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.68,0:07:54.62,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,but if we find it, \Nwe'll tell everyone about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.29,0:07:56.30,Default,Ogura,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.30,0:07:57.70,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,There's really \Nsomething like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:08:02.93,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We want to stop class 3's \Ncalamity ourselves, if possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.67,0:08:06.39,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,You two wanna come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.39,0:08:07.12,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.85,0:08:09.71,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,No thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.71,0:08:11.25,Default,Ogura,0,0,0,,Same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.02,0:08:15.85,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.80,0:08:21.32,Default,Ogura,0,0,0,,See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.32,0:08:23.08,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.42,0:08:34.57,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.57,0:08:36.00,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Where's Mochizuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.35,0:08:37.90,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.90,0:08:40.41,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I just got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.41,0:08:42.20,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:44.76,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I had nothing to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.76,0:08:46.86,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and I didn't want \Nto stay at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.86,0:08:49.43,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I figured I'd come here and draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.43,0:08:50.38,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.61,0:08:52.25,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,What about you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.25,0:08:55.37,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,And... Mochizuki's coming too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.86,0:08:58.30,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,What are you three going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.30,0:08:59.58,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.58,0:09:02.73,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Well... we're, uh... exploring?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.78,0:09:05.66,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Sorry, I'm late!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.54,0:09:13.73,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,And where do you \Nthree plan on exploring?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.73,0:09:14.84,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.84,0:09:19.12,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Well, Teshigawara said \Nwe should meet here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.12,0:09:21.37,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.37,0:09:22.78,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.78,0:09:25.66,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Sakaki said he had \Nto look for something!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:28.87,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,It's a bit important.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.38,0:09:34.75,Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fnWC Mano Negra Bta\c&H0D0406&\3c&H0D0406&\bord0.7\fsp1\be1\fs72\pos(525,513)}Do Not Enter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.69,0:09:37.21,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We don't know \Nwhat could happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.21,0:09:39.38,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,so I'd rather you \Nstayed in the club room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.68,0:09:41.61,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.61,0:09:43.00,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:46.08,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,You really are weird, Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.08,0:09:47.39,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Aren't you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.39,0:09:49.58,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,No, I don't think I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:18.61,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Which one is class 3's?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.61,0:10:20.14,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Probably the one in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.14,0:10:22.15,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,There are only five classrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.42,0:10:56.62,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,By the way, didn't this old building \Nhave like, seven mysteries or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.62,0:10:57.65,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:11:01.17,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I also don't give a shit \Nabout some urban legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.82,0:11:05.50,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So you don't believe in \Nghosts, curses, and the sort?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.50,0:11:07.31,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Hell no!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.53,0:11:10.04,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,They're all just coincidences \Nor tricks of the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.04,0:11:13.89,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Except for the calamity, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.89,0:11:18.78,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Isn't "the secret of the auxiliary library" \None of those seven mysteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.78,0:11:19.88,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.88,0:11:24.27,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,They say you can hear \Nsomeone's voice coming from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.27,0:11:25.64,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Have you heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.64,0:11:27.06,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:29.97,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,I heard there's an old \Narchive in its basement, {merge}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.97,0:11:32.69,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,containing secret writings that \Ncan't be revealed to the public,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.69,0:11:37.76,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,and that a librarian once locked \Nhimself inside to guard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.76,0:11:39.92,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So that librarian is still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.92,0:11:41.55,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,and you can hear his voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.55,0:11:45.55,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I bet it's just Chibiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.79,0:11:49.22,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I sometimes hear \Nvoices in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.87,0:11:50.84,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.84,0:11:51.93,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.89,0:11:54.94,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.57,0:11:58.90,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Let's let in some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.40,0:12:08.93,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You're not fine at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.92,0:12:14.87,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes, I am. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:17.34,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,You look fine to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.34,0:12:21.09,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,We wouldn't want anyone to see us and turn us into another one of the seven mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.44,0:12:23.66,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,So let's just keep \Nthe windows closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.68,0:12:40.40,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Teshigawara!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.52,0:12:45.36,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,You gotta be kidding me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.44,0:12:48.36,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You seem fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.16,0:12:56.25,Default,Ogura,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.59,0:12:58.04,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.04,0:13:00.73,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,I'll call you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.15,0:13:02.25,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.25,0:13:03.65,Default,Ogura,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.76,0:13:14.18,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,I can't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:18.95,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I don't think it'd be in an \Neasy-to-find place, like in a desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.95,0:13:21.49,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be in an \Nimpossible-to-find place, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.49,0:13:23.19,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,There'd be no point in leaving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.19,0:13:24.68,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.68,0:13:27.65,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,It's probably not on the \Nfloor, or in any desks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:29.78,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,What about in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.88,0:13:36.05,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,All I see are cleaning supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.21,0:13:38.00,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.65,0:13:42.67,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.60,0:13:46.88,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.11,0:13:49.02,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Something's written on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.02,0:13:50.41,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:58.06,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,"To the future students who are undoubtedly \Nsuffering from the senseless disaster of this class."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.06,0:13:59.14,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.14,0:14:00.30,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.30,0:14:03.00,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Mr. Matsunaga must \Nhave written that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.95,0:14:18.95,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnKozukaGothicProH-Madoka\c&H484639&\fay-0.22\bord4\blur1\fs72\3c&HA1ABAE&\pos(689,132)}A/V Room
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.66,0:14:25.38,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I think there's one in here. \NAre we allowed to use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.61,0:14:27.67,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,So long as no one finds out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.55,0:14:44.86,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.99,0:14:54.72,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,All right. Let's play it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:12.48,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:17.11,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}My... My name is \NMatsunaga Katsumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.11,0:15:22.16,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm a ninth grader \Nin 1983's class 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.16,0:15:23.74,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}When I'm done recording,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:27.34,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I plan on hiding this \Nsomewhere in the classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:30.08,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you're listening to this tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.08,0:15:37.05,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}then you're most \Nlikely in class 3 too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.05,0:15:40.85,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wonder if that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.60,0:15:41.41,Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnAdobe Hebrew\c&H21262A&\fs36\bord2\3a&H77&\blur2\pos(930,163)\3c&H6F7477&}Ayano
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.85,0:15:50.36,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}You may also be terrified by the \Nsenseless disaster that I—that we...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.66,0:15:44.65,Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnAdobe Hebrew\c&H21262A&\fs36\bord2\3a&H77&\blur2\pos(930,163)\3c&H6F7477&}Ayano
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.36,0:15:52.19,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}But never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.19,0:15:57.09,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have two reasons \Nfor leaving this tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.09,0:16:01.91,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}One is to confess a sin. My sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.91,0:16:04.46,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want to tell \Nsomeone what I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.46,0:16:06.36,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I want someone to listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:11.11,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}The other is to give \Nyou all some advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.65,0:16:14.95,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's about the extra student \Nwho gets mixed up in the class,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:17.77,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}the calamity that \Noccurs as a result,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:20.62,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}and how it can be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.62,0:16:22.97,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.97,0:16:27.22,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Actually, I should start \Nfrom the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.52,0:16:38.81,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our class went on a trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:42.93,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}We all left on August 8th, \Nfor three days and two nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.93,0:16:48.15,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our homeroom teacher, Mr. Koga, \Nsuggested that we visit a local shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.77,0:16:53.18,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's an old shrine in this town \Ncalled Yomiyama Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.18,0:16:55.43,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}He said that if we all prayed there,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.43,0:16:58.11,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}then the curse \Nwould surely be lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.52,0:17:01.96,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}There were 22 students \Ntotal, including myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.96,0:17:04.85,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}We were all skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.78,0:17:07.76,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}On the second day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.76,0:17:12.09,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}we climbed the mountain \Nto visit the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.03,0:17:15.74,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was very old and run-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.74,0:17:19.26,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}As if it had been \Nabandoned by the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:21.82,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even though it bears \Nthe name of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.82,0:17:24.35,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}it looked like it hadn't \Nbeen maintained at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.76,0:17:30.15,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}So while we were there, \Nwe decided to clean up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.15,0:17:36.32,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}At the time, we hoped that \Nmaybe this would lift the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.32,0:17:39.67,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}And after we prayed, \Nour teacher confidently declared,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.67,0:17:42.16,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Everything will be all right now."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.58,0:17:45.88,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.88,0:17:48.16,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}It wasn't that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.62,0:17:51.40,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}As soon as we left the shrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.40,0:17:55.20,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}the clear skies suddenly \Nturned overcast,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.20,0:17:56.80,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it began to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.80,0:17:59.42,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}There was even lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.42,0:18:01.57,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}We hurried down the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.57,0:18:05.14,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}The first victim was \Na boy named Hamaguchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.17,0:18:07.90,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was kind of dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.90,0:18:11.73,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was the only one \Nwho'd brought an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.46,0:18:15.08,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}And we were on a mountain, \Nduring a lightning storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.08,0:18:18.57,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was walking \Nin front of me, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.16,0:18:22.10,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}For a second, \Nmy vision went white,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.10,0:18:24.24,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I heard a huge crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.31,0:18:28.79,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hamaguchi had been \Nstruck by lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.79,0:18:32.25,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I still remember the smell \Nof his flesh burning...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.24,0:18:35.67,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Anyway, the students \Npanicked and bolted,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.10,0:18:38.60,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}leaving Hamaguchi behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.60,0:18:42.72,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were desperate to get off the \Nmountain as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.32,0:18:46.97,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Moments after we \Nblindly took off...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.43,0:18:50.95,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}The second victim was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.51,0:18:54.03,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}A girl named Hoshikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.49,0:18:56.40,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}In her panic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.40,0:19:01.61,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}she slipped and \Nfell off a tall, sheer cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.61,0:19:04.07,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}All we could do was call for help \Nat the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.23,0:19:09.16,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}But in the end, we couldn't \Nsave either of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.58,0:19:14.77,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Praying at the shrine \Nhad absolutely no effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.77,0:19:18.87,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, this is the important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:22.06,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right after we finally reached \Nthe bottom of the mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.06,0:19:24.06,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}that's when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.06,0:19:27.60,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}And by {\i0}it{\i1}, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.23,0:19:29.26,Default,Matsunaga,0,0,0,,{\i1}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.44,0:19:41.77,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.21,0:20:02.59,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.79,0:20:07.35,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I was in a cold sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:09.09,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.04,0:20:11.35,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,The tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.82,0:20:18.02,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.84,0:20:20.07,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:23.60,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,You've gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:26.31,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We didn't get to hear \Nthe important part!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.31,0:20:27.80,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,What should we do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.80,0:20:31.03,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,All we need to do is fix the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.03,0:20:32.73,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,It can be fixed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:34.78,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.78,0:20:36.58,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Great! Thanks, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.89,0:20:39.07,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,We've gotta hear the rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.07,0:20:40.96,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Do you mind if we \Nleave it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.46,0:20:45.09,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,I'll do what I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.21,0:21:26.59,Default,Ogura,0,0,0,,Brother!
